Description: shorter side of a length, cramping him for room as it angles in from middle stump. Hits Saha high on the glove in front his chest, with the ball dribbling towards the man at backward short leg
length ball on fifth stump, as Saha pushes at it but back to the bowler off the inside half of the bat
driven between mid-off and cover!Just uses the pace, and the ball races away though the quick outfield. Fullish ball and a bit wide of off, as he presents the full face of the bat
hacked just past point!The point fielder leaped to his right, but the ball was way above him. Short and wide from Boult, and Saha slashed hard
inside edge past the stumps!Saha going for everything here. Much fuller ball just outside off, as he seemed to have driven early at that. Single to fine leg
full just outside off, but finishes on off stump. Tucked to cover
good length ball, sliding into his pads. Clipped to short fine
short of a length, angling in late to finish on off. No room for Gill to nudge with a flat bat towards cover
length delivery in the channel outside off, and tucked back
there is a man somewhere between short mid-on and short midwicket, and Gill finds him with his flick off this full ball angling into the stumps
punches this shortish ball, shaping away to end just outside off. Finds the cover fielder
gets off the mark off the sixth ball. A little clip off the length ball on the stumps, and a single to deep square
belted back 90 degrees!Zampa tossed it up, and went full on the stumps. Pandya stood with his front leg out of the way, and sent that flying back
hacked hard to deep extra cover!Short and wide of off, and a rap hard with a flat bat
Remember Pandya vs Zampa from the ODI series in 2017? Pandya is giving us a flashback. Sees another loopy and full delivery on the stumps, and goes launching into it over the bowler's head
six more!Pandya is stone-faced, and why not? Stands outside leg, and deep in the crease, before clubbing this length ball around middle and leg back down the pitch
just a single, and a relief to my fingers. Short around off, and slapped to deep point
very full on the stumps, and pushed to deep midwicket. The over costs 24
short, wide of off, and quite slow. Turns away, as it is flashed to deep extra cover
good bounce, and some turn away. Good length on off, and goes away, as Pandya is surprised by the bounce while trying to push. Beaten there
shortish on off, and punched towards point
short outside off, and slapped to deep backward point. Two more, as Sandeep dives to cut that off to his left
very slow, and on a length. And four to deep backward point, as he hacks that very late. Sandeep from deep point can do little, as it's timed and placed beautifully
short again outside off, and now pumped to deep point's right
good length on middle and leg. Pushed to deep midwicket
length ball just outside off, and guided wide of short third
swatted to deep point!Boult from deep extra cover dived to his left, but couldn't stop that. Pandya saw the ball short and wide of off, and slammed that hard
full on leg with a curving action, and chipped to long-on
turns in off a good length to finish on middle. Clipped to midwicket
good length outside off, and slapped to deep point
pulled to deep midwicket, as the ball is short on middle, and turns away
swats this shortish ball outside off to long-off
full on middle and leg, and slog swept to fine leg
drives this full ball on middle to long-off to keep ticking
and Saha pushes it to long-off!Full and slow on the stumps, and a gentle nudge to wrap up a massive win.GT win by nine wickets, and with 37 balls to spare
the cover fielder dives to his left to save a few potential runs. Short of a length outside off, and punched back by Gill
now finds the man at cover with his drive, as this length ball arrives at fifth stump
trickles for four to deep point!Boult goes short, and angles it across, as the ball ends slightly wide of off. Gill rides the bounce, and slaps it to deep point
good length on middle and off, and nudged towards mid-on, as the bat turns in his hands
fuller side of a length on off, and pushed towards midwicket
guides this good length ball on off to the point fielder, as he opens the bat face late
good length on off, and punched to mid-off with a sweet sound off the bat
slower ball on a good length on off. Saha taps it close to the pitch on the off side, and takes off
stands outside leg, and skips down a bit to nudge this good length ball on middle and leg to long-on

appeal for leg before wicket by Sandeep, but not given. Sandeep and Samson get together, andRR review. Ah, replays show it was a knuckle ball. On a good length on middle and leg, slides down the leg side. Saha tries to swipe but is beaten, while being hit on his left thigh. No bat involved, and the impact was outside leg. So RR lose a review
quite full on off, and flicked to short midwicket
drilled wide of mid-off!Jumps out of the crease after making room, and converts the ball into a low full toss on the stumps. Presents the full face of the bat to send that whistling away
lofted over mid-on!A stylish shot, as the length ball angles across to end outside off. He holds the pose too, while swinging across the line
fuller, and wider of off. Driven to mid-off
good length on off, and clipped with a flat bat towards midwicket
chipped over mid-on!That looked effortless, even as Boult bowled at only 116kph. Lofts that with his back leg in the air, as the full ball arrived on the stumps
smacked between cover-point and extra cover!Too short and too wide outside off from Boult, and Saha gets on top of it to cut hard
good length on off, and clipped to deep square
length ball on leg, driven to short cover, who fumbles to allow a single
sliced over mid-off!He sat deep in the crease, and got a length ball outside off. He just lofted with an open face of the bat
good length ball just outside off, and finds cover with his punch
length ball on the stumps, as he backs away but ends up pushing it to Sandeep's left
swiped to deep midwicket!The fielder at midwicket dived to his right, but in vain. Short ball on middle, which angles in, but Gill makes room to swing that for four
backs away, and ends up fending this good length ball finishing outside leg after angling in to cover
turns in and keeps low right away to end on middle. Flicked to deep midwicket after getting across
now turns away off a good length, and ends around off. Pushed back to the bowler
short on off, and slapped to deep backward point. I am sure even Gill must have had no clue that it would end up as four, considering it was only placed nicely
very full and on the stumps. Driven to long-on
lands between short fine chasing to his left, and fine leg rushing forward. Saha tried to sweep this length ball turning in, but ended up ballooning
short again outside off. Hints to turn away, and is hacked to deep point
full on off, and driven to cover
turns away towards off from a good length on middle. Dabbed down to Chahal's right
much fuller on the stumps, and pushed to long-on
misses his sweep, as this length ball outside off is much slower while turning away
now the googly. Short outside off, and turning in. Slashed to point, where the fielder dives to his right and lets it dribble towards deep point
short again, and turning away towards off. A swipe between long-on and deep midwicket, as the former fielder slides to cut that off
very full, and a bit wide of off. Driven to deep point
short and quicker on middle. Punched back to the bowler
wow, that looked so elegant!Just a gentle drive to this full and loopy ball on off, and places it wide of long-off
keeps low off a shortish length on middle and off. Chopped towards cover
low full toss just outside off. Gets an inside edge on to his pad as he tries to flick
good length on the stumps. Goes deep and clips to deep square for a hurried two
short around off, and slashed to deep point
much slower, and with some loop. Full outside off, and turning further away, as Saha misses his slog sweep
full on the stumps, and flatter. Driven to long-off

stumped by Samson!Chahal has a few words to utter out. Now he slows it down to Gill too - like he has done to Saha today - and completely foxes Gill. It was a legspinner, pitched on a length on middle stump. Gill saw that tossed up and danced down the pitch, little realising that it was much slower than the previous balls. He missed, the ball turned well away, and Samson found him short
full on the stumps, and pushed to short cover
good length outside leg, and nudged towards deep midwicket
